    <summary>Privacy-first browser for Windows. Built-in AI security, no telemetry, open-source.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
## VELO Browser

VELO is a privacy-first browser for Windows built on WebView2 (Chromium engine).

### Key features

- **Shield Score** — visual security rating for every site (Red / Yellow / Green / Gold)
- **Real-time threat blocking** — trackers, malware, fingerprinting attempts
- **VELO Security Inspector** (`Ctrl+Shift+V`) — standalone window with TLS, tracker, AI and fingerprint details
- **Command Bar** (`Ctrl+K`) — fuzzy-search tabs, bookmarks, history, and commands
- **Glance link preview** — hover any link to preview it without loading it
- **Workspaces + Split View + Tab tear-off** — Arc-like UX
- **VeloAgent** — local AI assistant powered by Ollama or LLamaSharp (no cloud required)
- **Paste Protection + Anti-capture banking mode**
- **Portable mode** — run from USB drive, no install needed
- **Zero telemetry** — no crash reports, no usage data ever sent

### Requirements

- Windows 10 (1903+) or Windows 11
- Microsoft Edge WebView2 Runtime (pre-installed on Windows 11; installed automatically by this package on Windows 10)

### Notes

- The installer is an Inno Setup executable signed with Authenticode.
- VELO stores all data in `%LocalAppData%\VELO\` by default.
- For portable mode, place a `portable.flag` file next to `VELO.exe`.
    ]]></description>

